# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Atlas environment — copy to .env.local and fill in for backend work.
# The demo app runs with NONE of these set (data is in-memory).
#
# Each var is tagged:
#   [required]      — the app cannot boot without it, in ANY environment.
#   [required-prod] — optional in dev (the feature no-ops); REQUIRED in
#                     production. lib/env.ts fails the prod boot if missing.
#   [optional]      — tuning / local-only.
#
# lib/env.ts is the source of truth and validateEnv() enforces this on every
# production server boot. The Vercel env table in docs/runbooks/deploy.md §5
# must list every [required]/[required-prod] key.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase (Postgres + RLS + storage) — docs/02-architecture.md §3
# [required] Project URL + anon (public) key + service-role (server-only) key.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# [required] App runtime connection — Supabase TRANSACTION pooler (port 6543).
# Connections return to the pooler after each transaction; the postgres-js
# client sets prepare:false (transaction mode can't reuse prepared statements).
# Session mode (port 5432) pins one connection per client and exhausts the
# pooler's client cap under normal concurrency. (Connect → Transaction pooler in
# the Supabase dashboard.) In prod, validateEnv() requires the `:6543` port.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...@...pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
#
# [required-prod] Migrations-only connection — SESSION pooler / direct (port
# 5432). DDL runs in multi-statement transactions that need a session-pinned
# connection. In prod, validateEnv() requires the `:5432` port. (Dev migrates
# fine off DATABASE_URL, so this is optional locally.)
# DIRECT_URL=postgresql://...@...pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
#
# [optional] Per-process pool size (default 5). Lower to 1 on serverless
# (Vercel), where every instance opens its own pool against the shared cap.
# DB_POOL_MAX=5

# [required-prod] Public base URL. Used for links inside emails (invite/nudge
# CTAs point at ${APP_URL}/auth/confirm and ${APP_URL}/me) AND for robots.txt /
# sitemap.xml. Must be an https:// URL in production. Defaults to
# https://atlas.twistag.com for robots/sitemap and http://localhost:3000 for
# email links when unset in dev.
# APP_URL=https://atlas.twistag.com

# [optional] Local ephemeral Postgres for adversarial RLS tests. Leave unset and
# embedded-postgres boots one automatically; set to reuse a system Postgres.
# DATABASE_URL_TEST=

# Auth: Supabase Auth (native magic links + custom access-token hook), NOT
# Stytch — see docs/adrs/002-supabase-auth-not-stytch.md. No separate auth
# creds: it uses the Supabase keys above. The custom access-token hook
# (public.custom_access_token_hook, migration 0001) must be ENABLED in the
# Supabase dashboard, and two SMTP/template steps are needed for production
# sign-in email — see docs/runbooks/deploy.md §3 (and Resend below).

# [required-prod] Anthropic (Claude) — services/llm + services/conversation.
# Powers the conversation engine (session.start / session.sendMessage). Without
# it the LLM client throws LlmNotConfiguredError and those mutations return
# PRECONDITION_FAILED; in dev that's fine (conversation features disabled), in
# prod the IC sessions need it.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional: override the model. Defaults to claude-sonnet-4-6 (services/llm/client.ts).
# ATLAS_LLM_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Resend (transactional email) — services/email
# [required-prod] Invite + nudge emails go out via Resend directly (React Email
# templates). With no RESEND_API_KEY the send no-ops and logs `[email] skipped…`
# — fine in dev, but in prod that means SILENT non-delivery, so validateEnv()
# requires it.
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# [required-prod] EMAIL_FROM — the sender. Must NOT contain `resend.dev` (the
# sandbox sender spam-folders); use a verified-domain address. Falls back to the
# resend.dev sandbox in dev only.
# EMAIL_FROM="Atlas <atlas@atlas.twistag.com>"
#
# Sign-in magic-link email is sent by Supabase Auth, not this app. To make it
# production-ready, in the Supabase dashboard: (1) set Resend as the custom SMTP
# provider, (2) edit the Magic Link template to include {{ .Token }} (the 6-digit
# code) and bump the OTP/link expiry to 24h. See docs/runbooks/deploy.md §3/§4.

# [optional] Inngest (workers) — wired by plan 020. Until then the workers are
# inert; add these when 020 lands. Listed in the runbook §5 as a slot.
# INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=
# INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=

# [optional] Observability — wired by plan 023 (Sentry/OpenTelemetry). Add the
# DSN when 023 lands. Listed in the runbook §5 as a slot.
# SENTRY_DSN=
